This paper deals with the efficient decoding of an indexing for quadratic residues modulo N, which involves information theory and computational complexity. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
